    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Jonathan Bulkley was a member of the Ann Arbor Housing Commission (AAHC) from 1973 to 1976, and president of the commission from 1974 until 1976.</p>
      <p>Throughout his tenure as the Housing Commissioner, Bulkley oversaw the operation of an extremely troubled agency. Intense factionalism afflicted the commission's staff, and severe problems arose regarding several of the public housing sites administered by the body.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The Bulkley papers consist of his working files, including records of meetings, policy statements, and staff materials documenting the work of the Ann Arbor Housing Commission. The papers have been divided into three series: Ann Arbor Housing Commission meeting files; Policy statements and other materials; and Organizational files.</p>
    </scopecontent>
